passes leading box-based [24] and box-free [43] methods 
over 0.2% and 1.5% PQ, respectively. With simple en-
hancement, the gap enlarges to 0.9% and 2.2% PQ. Mean-
while, Panoptic FCN outperforms all top-ranking models 
on COCO test-dev set, as illustrated in Table 12. In par-
ticular, the proposed method surpasses the state-of-the-art
